President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire due to a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred from January 26-28, 2015. This declaration authorizes federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. The counties of Hillsborough, Rockingham, and Strafford are eligible for federal funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.